        "`goseg/handler/ship/backup.go` publishes multiple transition states (loading/success/error/clear) and ignores publish results, so UI/event consumers can miss status updates without any surfaced error."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Define and apply a single transition publish policy: either (a) propagate publish errors at operation boundaries, or (b) centralize best-effort publish with structured logging/metrics and explicit rationale. Replace raw `_ = Publish...` and unchecked publish calls with a shared helper that records dropped transition events consistently.",
